"code": "C"}, "type": "DIS", "enrollCapacity": 10, "primary": false, "number": "106", "waitlisted": 0, "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 5}, {"meetings": [{"dayAbbrvs": "Tu", "startTime": "10:00:00", "endTime": "10:59:00", "days": {"Tuesday": true, "Saturday": false, "Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Thursday": false, "Monday": false, "Wednesday": false}, "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 233", "code": "DWIN233"}, "instructors": []}], "id": 13454, "enrolled": 7, "status": {"description": "Closed", "code": "C"}, "type": "DIS", "enrollCapacity": 7, "primary": false, "number": "101", "waitlisted": 0, "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 4}, {"meetings": [{"dayAbbrvs": "Tu", "startTime": "12:00:00", "endTime": "12:59:00", "days": {"Tuesday": true, "Saturday": false, "Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Thursday": false, "Monday": false, "Wednesday": false}, "location": {"description": "Hearst Gym 242", "code": "HGYM242"}, "instructors": [{"role": null, "name": "Kellie Marie Powell"}]}], "id": 13455, "enrolled": 7, "status": {"description": "Open", "code": "O"}, "type": "DIS", "enrollCapacity": 10, "primary": false, "number": "102", "waitlisted": 2, "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 6}], "displayName": "BUDDSTD C50", "description": "This introduction to the study of Buddhism will consider materials drawn from various Buddhist traditions of Asia, from ancient times down to the present day. However, the course is not intended to be a comprehensive or systematic survey; rather than aiming at breadth, the course is designed around key themes such as ritual, image veneration, mysticism, meditation, and death. The overarching emphasis throughout the course will be on the hermeneutic difficulties attendant upon the study of religion in general, and Buddhism in particular. "}, "C224": {"meetings": [{"dayAbbrvs": "Tu", "startTime": "14:00:00", "endTime": "16:59:00", "days": {"Tuesday": true, "Saturday": false, "Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Thursday": false, "Monday": false, "Wednesday": false}, "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 288", "code": "DWIN288"}, "instructors": [{"role": null, "name": "Jacob  Dalton"}]}], "units": {"value": {}, "type": "discrete"}, "id": 13571, "title": "Readings in Tibetan Buddhist Texts", "sections": [{"meetings": [{"dayAbbrvs": "Tu", "startTime": "14:00:00", "endTime": "16:59:00", "days": {"Tuesday": true, "Saturday": false, "Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Thursday": false, "Monday": false, "Wednesday": false}, "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 288", "code": "DWIN288"}, "instructors": [{"role": null, "name": "Jacob  Dalton"}]}], "id": 13571, "enrolled": 4, "status": {"description": "Open", "code": "O"}, "type": "SEM", "enrollCapacity": 5, "primary": true, "number": "001", "waitlisted": 0, "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 5}], "displayName": "BUDDSTD C224", "description": "This seminar provides an introduction to a broad range of Tibetan Buddhist texts, including chronicles and histories, biographical literature, doctrinal treatises, canonical texts, ritual manuals, pilgrimage guides, and liturgical texts. It is intended for graduate students interested in premodern Tibet from any perspective. Students are required to do all of the readings in the original classical Tibetan. It will also serve as a tools and methods for the study of Tibetan Buddhist literature, including standard lexical and bibliographic references, digital resources, and secondary literature in modern languages. The content of the course will vary from semester to semester to account for the needs and interests of particular students."}, "C120": {"meetings": [{"dayAbbrvs": "TuTh", "startTime": "14:00:00", "endTime": "15:29:00", "days": {"Tuesday": true, "Saturday": false, "Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Thursday": true, "Monday": false, "Wednesday": false}, "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 229", "code": "DWIN229"}, "instructors": [{"role": null, "name": "Sanjyot  Mehendale"}]}], "units": {"value": {"units": 4.0}, "type": "fixed"}, "id": 13623, "title": "Buddhism on the Silk Road", "sections": [{"meetings": [{"dayAbbrvs": "TuTh", "startTime": "14:00:00", "endTime": "15:29:00", "days": {"Tuesday": true, "Saturday": false, "Sunday": false, "Friday": false, "Thursday": true, "Monday": false, "Wednesday": false}, "location": {"description": "Dwinelle 229", "code": "DWIN229"}, "instructors": [{"role": null, "name": "Sanjyot  Mehendale"}]}], "id": 13623, "enrolled": 20, "status": {"description": "Closed", "code": "C"}, "type": "LEC", "enrollCapacity": 20, "primary": true, "number": "001", "waitlisted": 4, "printInScheduleOfClasses": true, "waitlistCapacity": 15}], "displayName": "BUDDSTD C120", "description": "This course will discuss the social, economic, and cultural aspects of Buddhism as it moved along the ancient Eurasian trading network referred to as the \u201cSilk Road\u201d. Instead of relying solely on textual sources, the course will focus on material culture as it offers evidence concerning the spread of Buddhism. Through an examination of the Buddhist archaeological remains of the Silk Road, the course will address specific topics, such as the symbiotic relationship between Buddhism and commerce; doctrinal divergence; ideological shifts in the iconography of the Buddha; patronage (royal, religious and lay); Buddhism and political power; and art and conversion. All readings will be in English."}}